          <line>The Atreidae never would have acted thus.</line>
          <line>But noble is thy nature, and thy birth,</line>
          <line>And therefore little did my wretchedness,</line>
          <line>Nor from my wounds the noisome stench deter</line>
          <line>Thy generous heart. I have a little respite;</line>
          <line>Help me, my son I I'll try to rise; this weakness</line>
          <line>Will leave me soon, and then we'll go together.</line>
          <line>NEOPTOLEMUS</line>
          <line>I little thought to find thee thus restored.</line>
          <line>Trust me, I joy to see thee free from pain,</line>
          <line>And hear thee speak; the marks of death were on</line>
